Description: Figure plaque fragment of a terracotta of unknown type. Possibly mould-made part of a base. Made of pale orange-brown clay.
Curator's comments: See figure plaque fragments from Naukratis, dating to the Hellenistic period (Cambridge, Museum of Classical Archaeology NA371-2; NA376).
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (DB.384) (Phase 3)
